# CI Runner Convention

When writing or editing GitHub Actions workflow YAML, use these runner labels:

- **Basic Linux**: `runs-on: [self-hosted, linux, x64]`
- **Docker/Buildx**: `runs-on: [self-hosted, linux, x64, docker]`
- **Playwright**: `runs-on: [self-hosted, linux, x64, browser]`

Use `ubuntu-latest`, `windows-latest`, or `macos-latest` only for documented exceptions (Pages deploy, Release publishing, multi-OS smoke, ML publish). See `docs/src/ci/runner-contract.md`, `docs/src/ci/github-hosted-exceptions.md`, and `docs/src/ci/workflow-enumeration.md`.

**Env registry:** canonical `VOX_*` / Turso / orchestrator names — `docs/src/reference/env-vars.md` (redirect stubs: `docs/src/ref/env-vars.md`, `docs/src/ref/env-vars-ssot.md`).
